```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::ifstream inputFile("input.txt"); // Replace with your file name
    if (!inputFile) {
        std::cerr << "Error opening file." << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }
    std::string wordToCount("Example"); // Replace with the word you want to count
    int count = 0;

    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(inputFile, line)) {
        size_t pos = line.find(wordToCount);
        if (pos != std::string::npos) {
            count++;
        }
    }
    inputFile.close();

    std::cout << "The word '" << wordToCount << "' appears " << count << " times in the file." << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

In this program:
1. Replace "input.txt" with the actual name of the text file you want to read.
2. Replace "Example" with the specific word you want to count in the file.
3. The program uses std::getline to read each line of the file and then uses the find function to check if the wordToCount is present in that line.
4. Finally, the program reports the number of occurrences of the specified word.

Remember to compile and run the program with the appropriate file name and word to get the desired results.
